Process called "clear_all_breakpoints" that takes session as DebugSession returns Boolean:
    Note: Clear all active breakpoints and notify runtime system
    Let breakpoint_count be length of session.active_breakpoints Note: Notify each breakpoint is being removed
    For each breakpoint in session.active_breakpoints:
    Let removal_result be notify_runtime_breakpoint_removal with breakpoint as breakpoint
    If not removal_result["success"]:
    Note: Log warning but continue clearing
    Let warning_message be "Failed to remove breakpoint at " concatenated with breakpoint.file_path concatenated with ":" concatenated with breakpoint.line_number
    log_warning with message as warning_message Note: Clear the breakpoints list
    Set session.active_breakpoints to list containing Note: Update session metadata
    Set session.metadata["breakpoints_cleared_count"] to breakpoint_count
    Set session.metadata["last_clear_timestamp"] to get_current_timestamp Return breakpoint_count is greater than 0